          <updateDate>2017-05-17T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>School Infrastructure Modernization Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow rehabilitation expenditures for any building which is a qualified public educational facility to qualify for the rehabilitation tax credit. A &quot;qualified public educational facility&quot; is a school facility which is part of a public elementary or secondary school and is owned by a private, for-profit corporation pursuant to a public-private partnership agreement with a state or local educational agency.</p>]]></text>
